                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Dec. 16: Sebi today mandated all listed firms to disclose within 10 days any change in their shareholding pattern. Firms coming out with public offers will have to do the same a day before going public. In all cases wherein the change in capital structure because of such restructuring exceeds +/-2 per cent of the paid share capital, the listed entities shall file a revised shareholding pattern with the stock exchanges within 10 days of the allotment of shares, Sebi said.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 16: Food inflation reached 9.46 per cent during the week ended December 4 as vegetables turned expensive. Inflation stood at 8.69 per cent in the previous week and at 20.90 per cent in the corresponding week last year.                             
	 Mumbai, Dec. 16: GVK Power and Infrastructure today said private equity majors Actis and an affiliate of Singapore government-owned GIC would be investing nearly Rs 700 crore in its subsidiary GVK Energy.                             
	 Mumbai, Dec. 16: Shareholders and creditors of Essar Shipping, Ports and Logistics have given the nod for demerger of its shipping, logistics and oil fields business into a separate entity.                                                                                                                          
